        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical conditions and has been healthy throughout his childhood. He was born at full term via normal vaginal delivery with no perinatal complications. His immunization record is up to date including rotavirus vaccination in infancy. He has no history of prior hospitalizations or surgeries. {patientName} has a known mild penicillin allergy documented during a prior ear infection episode at age 5, which caused a skin rash. He has no known food allergies. He takes no regular prescription medications. His growth and developmental milestones have been appropriate for his age, and his last well-child visit was 4 months ago with normal findings. There is a paternal family history of inflammatory bowel disease. {patientName}'s mother reports that he occasionally experiences mild constipation but has never had a diarrheal illness of this severity before."
          }
        ]
      }
